history.text: Hello. Have you seen the 1975 movie, Jaws?
Yes I have, Have you?
Yes. I always think about that music. It's so haunting when you know Jaws is coming. lol
Yes, it is impressive that most of the time you don't even see the shark.
It isn't intended to be watched by kids, but I bet alot of kids have seen it.
Yes, that's true. It's up there as a scary thriller I think.
Kids today have seen a lot more scary movies than I ever did. My 9 year old grandson has seen it.
Absolutely Spielberg definitely knew how to make a movie with high ratings in 1975
Yes, I watched it when I was very young the music freaked me out.
I agree totally! He's a very talented director who still creates great stuff today.
Even Rotten Tomatoes gives it 97%
The movie seems to work because the characters seem relatable.
Yeah and an average of 9.2 out of 10. Impressive
It takes a simple scene, families at the beach on a holiday weekend. What could be worse to experience??
An unexpected shark attack ruins the perfect holiday.
They tried to say it was a boating accident in an attempt not to scare everyone
Remember the scene when the shark hunters were aboard the boat and they were drinking and singing and having fun then all of a sudden, Boom, jaws rammed the boat!
They caught a tiger shark and thought the problem was solved... little did they know
Oh, I remember. Some of those scenes are memorable for sure.
Yes it seems everyone is in disbelief that Jaws actually was real.
Richard Dreyfuss is still acting, right? Always liked him. I think Roy Schneider passed on though.
Richard Dreyfuss definitely did well as Matt Hooper in the movie.
I wonder if people try to find Amity Island where the movie fictionally takes place?

Good question. I'll have to Google it. 
Wasn't it the mayor in Jaws that didn't want to "scare" people so he wouldn't cancel the holiday festivities! Big mistake
In the movie they lay out a chum line, I wonder if that was necessary. Seems like Jaws like any boat
Lol. Yes. Some of the scenes were a bit much.
In the movie they attempt to use a shark cage. That made for an interesting scene.
Hooper was lucky to escape.
Yes, and now I've seen programs with divers in those cages. They're crazy!
They finally take him out with a oxygen tank explosion.
Yikes! I wonder if the 1975 Jaws movie could every be re-made modern day.
I doubt it would get 8.0/10 from IMBD
IMDB
The boats name was Orca, and they were hunting a shark.
Most likely yes. I like to make my own decisions about if a movie is worth watching or not.
Yes, the rating tends to just be a suggestion i suppose
There have been other shark movies that still don't top this one.
Steven Spielberg definitely knew how to impress the critics in 1975,
I liked how intense the scene where they are paddling back to shore is.
You feel like you are right there in the scene. In my case, I'm probably turning away so not to look.
Whatever makes you want to turn away is like an adrenaline rush that makes me want to watch more of the movie.
Overall I think Jaws is a great movie.
